# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EXAMPLE secrets file. Copy this to ".dev.vars" for LOCAL testing only.
# .dev.vars is git-ignored so your real secrets never get committed.
# In production, these are set with `wrangler secret put NAME` instead.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# From @BotFather when you create your bot:
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN="123456:ABC-your-bot-token-here"

# Your personal Telegram chat id (we'll find this together):
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID="123456789"

# Any random password you invent — Telegram sends it back so we know
# a webhook request is really from Telegram (protects your bot):
TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET="make-up-a-long-random-string"

# A GitHub fine-grained token (this repo only, Contents: read & write):
GITHUB_TOKEN="github_pat_your_token_here"
